{
  "manifest": {
    "schemaVersion": 1,
    "name": "twenty48",
    "title": "Twenty48",
    "entrypoint": "index.html",
    "bindings": [],
    "capabilities": ["state:persist"],
    "preferredSize": {
      "w": 4,
      "h": 5
    }
  },
  "files": {
    "README.md": "# twenty48\n\nA compact 2048 tile game showing off `state:persist` — best score and board\nsurvive a reload.\n\nSlide the numbered tiles, merge matching pairs, and try to reach the 2048 tile.\nIt's the one starter widget that exercises the write-back capability end to end.\n\n## Controls\n\n- **Arrow keys** or **WASD** to slide the whole board.\n- **Swipe** (touch) in any direction.\n- **New game** resets the board; your best score is kept.\n\nMatching tiles merge into their sum, at most once per tile per move (so a row\nof `[2, 2, 4]` slid left becomes `[4, 4]` and scores 4 — not `[8]`). After each\neffective move a new `2` (90%) or `4` (10%) appears. Reach 2048 for the win\nbanner, then keep going for a higher score.\n\n## How `state:persist` works\n\nThe widget declares `\"capabilities\": [\"state:persist\"]` in `widget.json`. That\ngate lets it use exactly two bridge messages (see `packages/host/src/bridge.ts`):\n\n- On boot it posts `{ v: 1, type: \"dashboard:getState\", requestId }`. The parent\n  replies `{ v: 1, type: \"dashboard:state\", requestId, state, version }` with the\n  last blob it saved for this widget (or `null` the first time).\n- After each move (debounced ~500ms, and immediately on a new best) it posts\n  `{ v: 1, type: \"dashboard:setState\", requestId, state }` with a tiny\n  (`< 1KB`) `{ best, score, board, won, over }` blob. The widget id is bound by\n  the host, so a widget can only ever read and write **its own** state.\n\nWithout the capability the parent answers `dashboard:error` with\n`capability_denied`; the game handles that (and a standalone open with no host\nat all) by running in-memory with `best = 0`. Every message uses the `v: 1`\nenvelope and anything without it is ignored — no network requests of any kind.\n\n---\n\nInstalls from the demo gallery like the other starter widgets. Adapted from the\nreference implementation's custom-widget templates.\n",
    "index.html": "<!doctype html>\n<!--\n  twenty48 — a compact 2048 tile game, and the one starter that exercises the\n  `state:persist` capability end-to-end. On boot it asks the parent for its\n  saved blob (dashboard:getState) and restores the best score plus any\n  in-progress board; after each effective move it writes a tiny blob back\n  (dashboard:setState). Both messages are gated by the \"state:persist\"\n  capability in widget.json — without it the parent replies capability_denied\n  and the game just runs in-memory with best = 0. No bindings, no network of\n  any kind: everything below is self-contained.\n-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n    <title>Twenty48</title>\n    <style>\n      :root {\n        color-scheme: dark;\n        /* Theme tokens: default to system Canvas/CanvasText, overridden by the\n           parent's dashboard:theme reply (--bg/--card/--text/--accent/--border).\n           The derived tokens read from --text so the pushed theme drives them. */\n        --bg: Canvas;\n        --card: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 8%, Canvas);\n        --text: CanvasText;\n        --accent: #edc22e;\n        --border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 22%, transparent);\n        --cell: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 14%, transparent);\n      }\n      * {\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n      }\n      html,\n      body {\n        height: 100%;\n        margin: 0;\n      }\n      body {\n        padding: 8px;\n        font-family: var(--font-sans, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif);\n        background: var(--bg);\n        color: var(--text);\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        gap: 6px;\n        touch-action: none;\n        user-select: none;\n        -webkit-user-select: none;\n      }\n      header {\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        gap: 6px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n      }\n      h1 {\n        margin: 0;\n        font-size: 1.1rem;\n        letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n        flex: 1;\n      }\n      .score {\n        text-align: center;\n        min-width: 52px;\n        padding: 3px 8px;\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        background: var(--card);\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n        line-height: 1.1;\n      }\n      .score b {\n        display: block;\n        font-size: 0.55rem;\n        text-transform: uppercase;\n        letter-spacing: 0.6px;\n        opacity: 0.7;\n        font-weight: 600;\n      }\n      .score span {\n        font-size: 0.95rem;\n        font-weight: 700;\n        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n      }\n      button {\n        font: inherit;\n        font-size: 0.8rem;\n        padding: 5px 10px;\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n        background: var(--card);\n        color: inherit;\n        cursor: pointer;\n      }\n      button:hover {\n        border-color: var(--accent);\n      }\n      /* The board is square and scales to the smaller of the remaining width /\n         height so it always fits the widget cell regardless of aspect ratio. */\n      #stage {\n        flex: 1 1 auto;\n        min-height: 0;\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n      }\n      #board {\n        position: relative;\n        width: min(100%, calc(100cqh - 0px));\n        aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;\n        max-width: 100%;\n        max-height: 100%;\n        padding: 2.6%;\n        border-radius: 8px;\n        background: var(--card);\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n      }\n      #stage {\n        container-type: size;\n      }\n      .grid {\n        position: absolute;\n        inset: 2.6%;\n        display: grid;\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);\n        grid-template-rows: repeat(4, 1fr);\n        gap: 3.2%;\n      }\n      .grid .bg {\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        background: var(--cell);\n      }\n      .tiles {\n        position: absolute;\n        inset: 2.6%;\n      }\n      .tile {\n        position: absolute;\n        /* Must match the bg grid: 4 tracks + 3 gaps of 3.2% → track = 22.6%.\n           Positioned via left/top (container-relative %) — translate % would\n           resolve against the TILE's own size and bunch everything up. */\n        width: 22.6%;\n        height: 22.6%;\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        font-weight: 700;\n        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n        font-size: 6cqmin;\n        background: #eee4da;\n        color: #776e65;\n        transition:\n          left 90ms ease,\n          top 90ms ease,\n          background 90ms ease;\n        will-change: left, top;\n      }\n      .tile.pop {\n        animation: pop 120ms ease;\n      }\n      @keyframes pop {\n        0% {\n          transform: scale(0.1);\n        }\n        100% {\n          transform: scale(1);\n        }\n      }\n      .tile.merged {\n        animation: merged 120ms ease;\n      }\n      @keyframes merged {\n        0% {\n          transform: scale(1);\n        }\n        50% {\n          transform: scale(1.16);\n        }\n        100% {\n          transform: scale(1);\n        }\n      }\n      /* Overlay for game-over / win — sits above the tiles. */\n      #overlay {\n        position: absolute;\n        inset: 0;\n        border-radius: 8px;\n        display: none;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        gap: 8px;\n        background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--bg) 78%, transparent);\n        text-align: center;\n      }\n      #overlay.show {\n        display: flex;\n      }\n      #overlay p {\n        margin: 0;\n        font-size: 1.1rem;\n        font-weight: 700;\n      }\n      footer {\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        font-size: 0.62rem;\n        opacity: 0.6;\n        text-align: center;\n      }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <header>\n      <h1>Twenty48</h1>\n      <div class=\"score\"><b>Score</b><span id=\"score\">0</span></div>\n      <div class=\"score\"><b>Best</b><span id=\"best\">0</span></div>\n      <button id=\"new\" type=\"button\">New game</button>\n    </header>\n    <div id=\"stage\">\n      <div id=\"board\">\n        <div class=\"grid\" id=\"grid\"></div>\n        <div class=\"tiles\" id=\"tiles\"></div>\n        <div id=\"overlay\">\n          <p id=\"overlay-text\"></p>\n          <button id=\"overlay-btn\" type=\"button\">New game</button>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <footer>sandboxed · no network · state:persist</footer>\n\n    <script>\n      \"use strict\";\n\n      // ---- postMessage bridge helpers (v1 envelope, see packages/host/src/bridge.ts) ----\n      var reqSeq = 0;\n      function nextReqId() {\n        return \"t48-\" + Date.now().toString(36) + \"-\" + reqSeq++;\n      }\n      function post(type, extra) {\n        window.parent.postMessage(Object.assign({ v: 1, type: type }, extra || {}), \"*\");\n      }\n\n      // ---- game state ----\n      var SIZE = 4;\n      var board = emptyBoard(); // 4x4 of numbers (0 = empty)\n      var score = 0;\n      var best = 0;\n      var won = false; // 2048 reached and banner acknowledged (keep playing)\n      var over = false;\n      var tileEls = {}; // id -> element, so tiles animate (slide) between moves\n      var nextTileId = 1;\n\n      function emptyBoard() {\n        var b = [];\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++) b.push([0, 0, 0, 0]);\n        return b;\n      }\n\n      // Each cell can hold {value, id} once rendered; we track ids on a parallel\n      // grid so a moved tile keeps its DOM node and CSS-transitions to its new spot.\n      var ids = emptyBoard();\n\n      function spawnTile() {\n        var free = [];\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)\n          for (var c = 0; c < SIZE; c++) if (board[r][c] === 0) free.push([r, c]);\n        if (!free.length) return null;\n        var pick = free[(Math.random() * free.length) | 0];\n        board[pick[0]][pick[1]] = Math.random() < 0.9 ? 2 : 4;\n        ids[pick[0]][pick[1]] = nextTileId++;\n        return pick;\n      }\n\n      // ---- move logic (correct 2048 merge: at most one merge per tile per move) ----\n      // Collapse a single line toward index 0. Returns {line, gained, moved}.\n      function collapse(values) {\n        var filtered = values.filter(function (v) {\n          return v !== 0;\n        });\n        var out = [];\n        var gained = 0;\n        for (var i = 0; i < filtered.length; i++) {\n          if (i + 1 < filtered.length && filtered[i] === filtered[i + 1]) {\n            var sum = filtered[i] * 2;\n            out.push(sum);\n            gained += sum;\n            i++; // consume the partner so it can't merge again this move\n          } else {\n            out.push(filtered[i]);\n          }\n        }\n        while (out.length < SIZE) out.push(0);\n        var moved = false;\n        for (var j = 0; j < SIZE; j++)\n          if (out[j] !== values[j]) {\n            moved = true;\n            break;\n          }\n        return { line: out, gained: gained, moved: moved };\n      }\n\n      // Read a line from the board for a direction, apply collapse, write back.\n      // dir: 0=left, 1=right, 2=up, 3=down. Returns {moved, gained, reached2048}.\n      function move(dir) {\n        var moved = false;\n        var gained = 0;\n        var reached = false;\n        for (var k = 0; k < SIZE; k++) {\n          var coords = lineCoords(dir, k);\n          var vals = coords.map(function (rc) {\n            return board[rc[0]][rc[1]];\n          });\n          var res = collapse(vals);\n          if (res.moved) moved = true;\n          gained += res.gained;\n          for (var i = 0; i < SIZE; i++) {\n            board[coords[i][0]][coords[i][1]] = res.line[i];\n            if (res.line[i] >= 2048) reached = true;\n          }\n        }\n        return { moved: moved, gained: gained, reached2048: reached };\n      }\n\n      // The 4 board coordinates of \"line\" k, ordered from the direction's leading\n      // edge (index 0 = where tiles pile up). left/right walk columns; up/down rows.\n      function lineCoords(dir, k) {\n        var out = [];\n        for (var i = 0; i < SIZE; i++) {\n          if (dir === 0)\n            out.push([k, i]); // left: row k, cols 0..3\n          else if (dir === 1)\n            out.push([k, SIZE - 1 - i]); // right\n          else if (dir === 2)\n            out.push([i, k]); // up: col k, rows 0..3\n          else out.push([SIZE - 1 - i, k]); // down\n        }\n        return out;\n      }\n\n      function anyMovesLeft() {\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)\n          for (var c = 0; c < SIZE; c++) {\n            if (board[r][c] === 0) return true;\n            if (c + 1 < SIZE && board[r][c] === board[r][c + 1]) return true;\n            if (r + 1 < SIZE && board[r][c] === board[r + 1][c]) return true;\n          }\n        return false;\n      }\n\n      function doMove(dir) {\n        if (over) return;\n        // move() rewrites the board in place; ids no longer map to the merged\n        // layout, so we rebuild ids fresh from the collapsed board for rendering.\n        var before = board.map(function (row) {\n          return row.slice();\n        });\n        var res = move(dir);\n        if (!res.moved) {\n          board = before; // no effective move — restore and ignore\n          return;\n        }\n        score += res.gained;\n        if (score > best) {\n          best = score;\n          saveState(true); // new best is worth an immediate write\n        }\n        reindexIds();\n        var spawned = spawnTile();\n        render(spawned);\n        if (res.reached2048 && !won) {\n          won = true;\n          showOverlay(\"You made 2048! Keep going →\");\n        } else if (!anyMovesLeft()) {\n          over = true;\n          showOverlay(\"Game over — score \" + score);\n        }\n        saveState(false); // debounced write of the new board/score\n      }\n\n      // Assign a fresh id to every occupied cell after a collapse. We intentionally\n      // do NOT try to preserve slide-source identity (that needs per-tile origin\n      // tracking); tiles cross-fade/pop into place, which reads cleanly at this size.\n      function reindexIds() {\n        var fresh = emptyBoard();\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)\n          for (var c = 0; c < SIZE; c++) if (board[r][c] !== 0) fresh[r][c] = nextTileId++;\n        ids = fresh;\n      }\n\n      // ---- rendering ----\n      // Fixed hue scale that keeps readable text contrast on both light and dark.\n      var COLORS = {\n        2: [\"#eee4da\", \"#776e65\"],\n        4: [\"#ede0c8\", \"#776e65\"],\n        8: [\"#f2b179\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        16: [\"#f59563\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        32: [\"#f67c5f\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        64: [\"#f65e3b\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        128: [\"#edcf72\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        256: [\"#edcc61\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        512: [\"#edc850\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        1024: [\"#edc53f\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n        2048: [\"#edc22e\", \"#fff8f0\"],\n      };\n      function colorFor(v) {\n        return COLORS[v] || [\"#3c3a32\", \"#fff8f0\"];\n      }\n      function applyPos(el, r, c) {\n        // Container-relative placement matching the bg grid: 22.6% track + 3.2% gap.\n        var step = 22.6 + 3.2;\n        el.style.left = c * step + \"%\";\n        el.style.top = r * step + \"%\";\n      }\n\n      var tilesEl = document.getElementById(\"tiles\");\n      function render(spawned) {\n        var seen = {};\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)\n          for (var c = 0; c < SIZE; c++) {\n            var v = board[r][c];\n            if (v === 0) continue;\n            var id = ids[r][c];\n            seen[id] = true;\n            var el = tileEls[id];\n            if (!el) {\n              el = document.createElement(\"div\");\n              el.className = \"tile\";\n              tilesEl.appendChild(el);\n              tileEls[id] = el;\n            }\n            applyPos(el, r, c);\n            el.textContent = v;\n            var col = colorFor(v);\n            el.style.background = col[0];\n            el.style.color = col[1];\n            el.classList.remove(\"pop\", \"merged\");\n            // force reflow so re-adding the animation class restarts it\n            void el.offsetWidth;\n            if (spawned && spawned[0] === r && spawned[1] === c) el.classList.add(\"pop\");\n          }\n        // drop tiles no longer present\n        for (var key in tileEls) {\n          if (!seen[key]) {\n            tilesEl.removeChild(tileEls[key]);\n            delete tileEls[key];\n          }\n        }\n        document.getElementById(\"score\").textContent = score;\n        document.getElementById(\"best\").textContent = best;\n      }\n\n      function buildGrid() {\n        var grid = document.getElementById(\"grid\");\n        for (var i = 0; i < SIZE * SIZE; i++) {\n          var bg = document.createElement(\"div\");\n          bg.className = \"bg\";\n          grid.appendChild(bg);\n        }\n      }\n\n      var overlay = document.getElementById(\"overlay\");\n      function showOverlay(text) {\n        document.getElementById(\"overlay-text\").textContent = text;\n        overlay.classList.add(\"show\");\n      }\n      function hideOverlay() {\n        overlay.classList.remove(\"show\");\n      }\n\n      function newGame() {\n        board = emptyBoard();\n        ids = emptyBoard();\n        score = 0;\n        won = false;\n        over = false;\n        for (var key in tileEls) {\n          tilesEl.removeChild(tileEls[key]);\n          delete tileEls[key];\n        }\n        spawnTile();\n        spawnTile();\n        hideOverlay();\n        render(null);\n        saveState(false);\n      }\n\n      // ---- state:persist (dashboard:getState / dashboard:setState) ----\n      var saveTimer = null;\n      var haveState = false; // did the parent ever answer? (else run in-memory)\n      function serialize() {\n        // Tiny blob (<1KB): best + the current board + score, ids rebuilt on load.\n        return { best: best, score: score, board: board, won: won, over: over };\n      }\n      function saveState(immediate) {\n        if (saveTimer) {\n          clearTimeout(saveTimer);\n          saveTimer = null;\n        }\n        var doSave = function () {\n          saveTimer = null;\n          post(\"dashboard:setState\", { requestId: nextReqId(), state: serialize() });\n        };\n        if (immediate) doSave();\n        else saveTimer = setTimeout(doSave, 500);\n      }\n\n      function restore(state) {\n        haveState = true;\n        if (!state || typeof state !== \"object\") return false;\n        if (typeof state.best === \"number\") best = state.best;\n        var b = state.board;\n        var ok =\n          Array.isArray(b) &&\n          b.length === SIZE &&\n          b.every(function (row) {\n            return Array.isArray(row) && row.length === SIZE;\n          });\n        if (ok) {\n          board = b.map(function (row) {\n            return row.slice();\n          });\n          score = typeof state.score === \"number\" ? state.score : 0;\n          won = !!state.won;\n          over = !!state.over;\n          reindexIds();\n          render(null);\n          if (over) showOverlay(\"Game over — score \" + score);\n          document.getElementById(\"best\").textContent = best;\n          return true;\n        }\n        document.getElementById(\"best\").textContent = best;\n        return false;\n      }\n\n      // ---- theme ----\n      // Relative luminance (0..1) of a #rgb / #rrggbb color; null for anything non-hex.\n      function hexLuminance(value) {\n        if (typeof value !== \"string\" || value.charAt(0) !== \"#\") return null;\n        var hex = value.slice(1);\n        if (hex.length === 3) hex = hex[0] + hex[0] + hex[1] + hex[1] + hex[2] + hex[2];\n        if (!/^[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/.test(hex)) return null;\n        var r = parseInt(hex.slice(0, 2), 16);\n        var g = parseInt(hex.slice(2, 4), 16);\n        var b = parseInt(hex.slice(4, 6), 16);\n        return (0.2126 * r + 0.7152 * g + 0.0722 * b) / 255;\n      }\n\n      function applyTheme(tokens) {\n        if (!tokens) return;\n        var root = document.documentElement.style;\n        [\"--bg\", \"--card\", \"--text\", \"--accent\", \"--border\"].forEach(function (k) {\n          if (tokens[k]) root.setProperty(k, tokens[k]);\n        });\n        // Follow the pushed background's luminance so native UI (scrollbars, form\n        // controls) picks the matching scheme; skip when --bg isn't a hex color.\n        var lum = hexLuminance(tokens[\"--bg\"]);\n        if (lum !== null) root.colorScheme = lum < 0.5 ? \"dark\" : \"light\";\n      }\n\n      // ---- inbound messages (ignore anything without the v:1 envelope) ----\n      var stateReqId = nextReqId();\n      window.addEventListener(\"message\", function (event) {\n        var msg = event.data;\n        if (!msg || msg.v !== 1) return;\n        if (msg.type === \"dashboard:theme\") {\n          applyTheme(msg.tokens);\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:state\") {\n          // reply to our getState (or the echo of a setState). Only the first,\n          // matching our boot getState, seeds the board.\n          if (!haveState && msg.requestId === stateReqId) {\n            if (!restore(msg.state)) {\n              if (isBoardEmpty()) newGame();\n            }\n          }\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:error\") {\n          // capability_denied (state:persist off) or similar — fall back to\n          // in-memory play so the game still works when opened standalone.\n          if (!haveState) {\n            haveState = true;\n            if (isBoardEmpty()) newGame();\n          }\n        }\n      });\n\n      function isBoardEmpty() {\n        for (var r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)\n          for (var c = 0; c < SIZE; c++) if (board[r][c] !== 0) return false;\n        return true;\n      }\n\n      // ---- input: arrow keys + WASD ----\n      var KEYS = {\n        ArrowLeft: 0,\n        ArrowRight: 1,\n        ArrowUp: 2,\n        ArrowDown: 3,\n        a: 0,\n        d: 1,\n        w: 2,\n        s: 3,\n        A: 0,\n        D: 1,\n        W: 2,\n        S: 3,\n      };\n      window.addEventListener(\"keydown\", function (e) {\n        if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(KEYS, e.key)) {\n          e.preventDefault();\n          doMove(KEYS[e.key]);\n        }\n      });\n\n      // ---- input: touch swipe ----\n      var touchStart = null;\n      var boardEl = document.getElementById(\"board\");\n      boardEl.addEventListener(\n        \"touchstart\",\n        function (e) {\n          var t = e.changedTouches[0];\n          touchStart = { x: t.clientX, y: t.clientY };\n        },\n        { passive: true },\n      );\n      boardEl.addEventListener(\n        \"touchend\",\n        function (e) {\n          if (!touchStart) return;\n          var t = e.changedTouches[0];\n          var dx = t.clientX - touchStart.x;\n          var dy = t.clientY - touchStart.y;\n          touchStart = null;\n          var ax = Math.abs(dx);\n          var ay = Math.abs(dy);\n          if (Math.max(ax, ay) < 24) return; // too small to be a swipe\n          if (ax > ay) doMove(dx > 0 ? 1 : 0);\n          else doMove(dy > 0 ? 3 : 2);\n        },\n        { passive: true },\n      );\n\n      // ---- wire up + boot ----\n      document.getElementById(\"new\").onclick = newGame;\n      document.getElementById(\"overlay-btn\").onclick = newGame;\n      buildGrid();\n\n      // Announce, request theme, and ask for our persisted blob. If no host is\n      // listening (standalone open) nothing replies — start a game after a beat.\n      post(\"dashboard:ready\");\n      post(\"dashboard:getTheme\", { requestId: nextReqId() });\n      post(\"dashboard:getState\", { requestId: stateReqId });\n      setTimeout(function () {\n        if (!haveState && isBoardEmpty()) newGame();\n      }, 400);\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"
  }
}
